# Tests & quality gate

- Behavior changes require tests (backend pytest, frontend vitest, UI smoke when relevant).
- Order: narrow targeted tests → module regression → full suite if time allows.
- Cover positive, negative, edge, and regression cases; do not weaken assertions to green CI.

## City GO specifics

- Route/catalog: assert low-value categories and `service_only` / non-route-eligible places do not leak into public routes or catalogs.
- Admin UI: loading, disabled, error, success, and data refresh after writes.
- API: contract shape, auth (401/403), and service-level logic — not only status codes.

## Commands

```bash
.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/<file> -q --no-cov
cd frontend && npm test -- --run <pattern>
cd frontend && npm run build
```

If a test cannot run locally, state why and give the exact command for CI.
